race.comment: FELIS CHAUS (6) deep into the prep now and can find form quickly from the good barrier. Covered plenty of ground when a fading eighth over 1400m at Hawkesbury. Can stalk the speed and pounce late. LIGHTNING GLORY (1) scored a sharp win on debut at Newcastle, before heading to town for a wilting fifth over 1300m at Randwick on the soft (7) surface. Was slow to recover on that occasion and capable of returning to form with the 3kg claim. Shapes as the main danger. RHEGION (3) returns from a five-month layoff with some respectable provincial form. Ready to go after the two trials and has the figures to win this. VIN SANTO (4) just over six-weeks between runs when a tidy third over 1200m at this track. Has further upside and assess on his good win two-back at Kembla. BOLD AND BLAZEN (2) got off the mark last start at Gosford but doesn't get the same run today. Minor claims.
